<br>
Days passed, And Nathomin found his way back to the lands of Kunark. The House T'Vlos had converged there again... It was almost instinct for them, they traveled, and from great distances they found themselves gravitating together..<br>
Nathomin hunted with strangers and fellows for long days.. His mind blured to most everything around him.. Words echoed inside of his head... Malaehi's words. Her acusations of his crime against her.<br>
<br>
And his heart grew heavier with guilt. But even then the immage of her face, the taste of her lips... the vision of them together would bannish the darkness in his heart like the sun of midday could bannish the night, only to be covered again like clouds by grief for what he had done.<br>
<br>
His blades never lost their movement, never lost their tempo, they danced under the sun, gleeming cold steel and the red of his enemies blood.<br>
<br>
There were times when he could almost hear the chants of ancient warriors, The songs of battle sung to the one he called The Blade Master, To the God of War.... but he was denyed such honor as to sing them. He was a shadow walker... a rogue, a thief.<br>
<br>
He had not the right to call out to the Blade Master...<br>
<br>
But one day his blades did stop, they fell to his sides even as the creature before him clawed and kicked at him... Nathomin felt her presence... He knew she was here in the lands with him even as he heard the battle cry of the Coeur ringing out over the hills in Malaehi's clarion voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ssus'zhar....&quot; Nathomin whispered, all of his guilt flooded away to be replaced by a longing..<br>
<br>
Nathomin fell back propelled by a strong hit from the Sarnak that had taken the oppertunity while the rogue stood dumbfounded, And the force of the blow snapped Nathomin's mind back to the battle.<br>
<br>
His blades found new strength... a speed that he hadnt thought he could produce without the aid of magic... The Sarnak fell back under the flurry of cuts and slices.. And within moments... fell to the ground dead.<br>
<br>
Nathomin stepped over its body unmindfull of the coin and treasure it held and began running toward where He thought he heard Malaehi's voice....<br>
<br>
Up the hill, toward the Burning wood... She is HERE!!<br>
<br>
His heart was beating fast, hope flooded him and his stomach was fluttering. He laughed into the wind as he ran, blades at his side. He could look upon her face again... He could tell her all that he had felt and all the things his heart did when she was close to him.<br>
<br>
He could tell her..... that he Loved her....<br>
<br>
Malaehi was there. A druid sat nearby talking of comrads that were far away and they looked up warily when they saw the aproaching Tier'Dal. A frown creased the lips of the druidess as he came towards them, then Malaehi let out a cry of joy.<br>
<br>
&quot;NATHOMIN!!..&quot;<br>
<br>
Malaehi stood and ran to him, unmindfull of her companion's dour look.<br>
<br>
They fell into each others arms, words of greeting mumbled into each others shoulders. Nathomin's heart pounded in his chest as his mind raced.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sun-runner... I must speak with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Nathomin stood back and knelt at her feet, his eyes looking up into hers speaking all of the things he felt for her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Malaehi... My Sun-runner... I have done you wrongly, and for this I will not ask forgiveness.&quot;<br>
<br>
Malaehi opened her mouth to speak, but Nathomin shook his head to silence her. He had to say everything before he lost courage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Malaehi... My Sun-runner... I cannot marry you.. for so many reasons we both know.. And you have so much to learn about passion and so much to teach about love. I cannot promise that I will be there for all of it. but I ... Malaehi .. I wish to be with you, to help you...<br>
<br>
Malaehi.. Ssus'zhar.. I want to walk by your side... Please tell me I can walk with you.. &quot; Nathomin's voice dropped as he whispered. But Malaehi's delecate ears heard well enough, and the words took her breath away...<br>
<br>
&quot;Malaehi... I love you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Malaehi looked into Nathomin's eyes seeking any sign of deception, any trace of Tier'Dal lies.. but there were none.<br>
Nathomin's face held only desire and hope... she stood a moment, her heart pounding, her mind trying to sort out her thoughts.. franticly she looked around for something.. she knew not what... Her eyes settled back to his, tears of joy fell to her cheeks and she nodded.<br>
<br>
In that moment, as he felt her take breath to answer darkness fell over him.. and his legs crumpled beneath him... He felt a wave of hate descend upon him and he knew something was not right.<br>
<br>
He heard an echoing laughter in his head.. it was cruel and malicious... it knew no compassion, nor did it know the feelings mortals know...<br>
<br>
&quot;Innoruuk.....&quot; Nathomin whispered in dread... &quot;No... No innoruuk...Let me go!&quot; <br>
<br>
Nathomin's mind screamed out against the pull, cried out against the injustice... cried out for his love... Malaehi.<br>
Suddenly the darkness was thrown back, the hand lifted from him and his spirit fell back into his body... But his mind was spinning in terror and fury.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why... Why would you prevent me from being with her?&quot;<br>
Nathomin knew in that instant that his heart.... that which he had thought Innoruuk's gift/curse was not innoruuk's makeing at all.... That his ability to know hate AND passion... were not innoruuk's gift... but something he had had always... something that was Nathomin's... Innoruuk had lied to him.. <br>
<br>
Nathomin's eyes found focus and they found Malaehi and the Druidess both.. but his eyes were filled with anger.  He turned away from them so that they would not see how he hated...<br>
A scream built up within him... one born of fury and indignation, built of them but powered by his love for Malaehi..<br>
<br>
&quot;INNORUUK!!!!... YOU SHRIVELED SEEDLESS ARSE!!&quot;<br>
Nathomin breathed deeply as Malaehi stood shocked behind him, reaching out to still him... But he would not forgive this. Could not...<br>
<br>
&quot;I swore an oath Innoruuk. I swore that I would leave the realms of the gods to themselves.... But the Deal is OFF INNORUUK.... I will come to your very house and I will watch it burn... You have tried to take from me... My one joy... It will not happen again You vile gutless pile of Dung!&quot;<br>
<br>
Nathomin's voice echoed through the Burning Woods as he shouted this last..<br>
<br>
&quot;HEAR ME INNORUUK.... I AM NO LONGER YOUR CREATURE... NO MORE!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Nathomin turned to face Malaehi, her eyes were filled with tears, but her sweet lips were smileing as she enveloped him in an embrace.. She mumbled into his hair..<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes my shadow-lover.. Yes.. I want you to walk by my side.&quot;<br>
