Usst Ssins’Veldre I cannot do this any longer. Every night before I camp, I am summoned before the Ancients of Erollisi Marr and am interrogated. They keep me awake all night, beating me with their accusations, their prying eyes, their questions of where I've been, who was I with... I have denied my passion, denied my love, denied my actions to them... but I can lie NO more! <br>
<br>
Not only that, upon entering the Lion’s Hall, I am greeted with a cool response and peering eyes. The walls echo with whispers, I do not feel at home here anymore. I know that they KNOW what has happened to me. Then, it happened. When leaving the room after a meeting, I caught the cold look from Eranendi ... the one who came valiantly to my aid in times past, stood firm next to my side when I needed support and guidance. <br>
<br>
Aye, as I was leaving a meeting yesterday, he glared at me and called me “Teir’dal”. The others around either heard nothing or just chose to wander off, wordlessly. I ran from there in tears... The druidess, who knows, pulled me aside and warned me of the path I have chosen. She spoke of the wrath my Lord Mallo would have should this be found out.<br>
<br>
Then, today... you and that forked tongued Jyssa joined the hunting party with the Lions to invade Kaesora. You and I had to hunt together... as if... as if NONE of this has passed between us... Do you think the others were blind to the passion that was in your eyes?!<br>
<br>
I cannot live like this any longer... the agony.. the shame... and what... what is this feeling inside I have... it will not go away. My prayers are not being heard... there is no contact from my sisters... I feel utterly...<br>
<br>
lost...<br>
<br>
