<br>
Within minutes she saw Nathomin running swiftly to her, his long hair flying, free from it’s knot. With daggers still in hand and his blue skin shining from the efforts of his recent battle, Nathomin rushed into Malaehi’s arms, kissing her passionately. After a few breathless moments, the rogue pulled away with a chuckle as he sheathed his weapons and watched his love blush madly, still unused to such displays of passion. He took her hand and said: <br>
<br>
“Come my love, your Goddess has granted me this beautiful day and this feeling of love in my heart. I wish to celebrate love... keeping you blushing for the entire evening and glowing for days to come yet.” Malaehi gasped and felt herself being dragged along behind the rogue who was determinedly headed for his camp. He stopped and turned her back into his embrace, eyes sparkling with sheer joy. <br>
<br>
“I love you.... incredibly so much, Malaehi! I love the Goddess you serve as well, for she has opened my eyes to the true beauty of this land and of this life.” He turned his eyes up to the sky, pulled back from the embrace and proudly saluted “Hail Erollisi Marr, Queen of Love, the source of the happiness I feel now!”<br>
<br>
Malaehi felt a cold chill up her spine, and turned to face the cold North wind, hearing the haunting voice in her head again sneering “Death comes to you soon, Malaehi, you have broken your vows.“ Nathomin was so caught up in the joy of the moment that he failed to see her freeze in terror. <br>
<br>
“What is this, the rogue forsaking Innoruuk for His antithesis?” the wicked laughter continued “He speeds his death as a traitor, Malaehi, his fate is now sealed, as is yours”.<br>
<br>
“Nooo!” Malaehi screamed to the voice in her mind. Just as Nathomin turned in shock to question, a Giant lumbered over the hill and kicked Nathomin in the back. Stunned and without weapons in hand, the rogue stood dazed as the Giant pounded on him mercilessly. Malaehi quickly fought the Giant, casting a spell to destroy it's brain, then chanting for roots to come out of the earth to immobilize him so they could escape. Malaehi quickly grabbed her stunned lover and raced up the hill and into the tunnel.<br>
<br>
The emerged into the Frontier Mountains, safe at last. With daggers in hand and a fierce look of revenge on his face, Nathomin headed back to kill the giant. <br>
<br>
“Please don’t... Nathomin, another will come along and finish the job... I wish to speak with you.” Nathomin sighed, sheathed his weapons and let it go, finally noticing something strange in Mala. <br>
<br>
“Sunrunner, what is it?” Malaehi walked out of the tunnel, down the hill and started to make her way up the steep, jagged cliff of the Guardian’s mountain. Nathomin sensed Malaehi’s serious mood and chose to follow without question. After the strenuous climb, they arrived at the peak. Malaehi stumbled, feeling a bit dizzy form the height and this overwhelming fear that gripped her. Nathomin quickly caught her, pulling her into his protective embrace “What is it, Sunrunner?” <br>
<br>
Mala pulled away nervously, “Thh... this is a beautiful place is it not...?” Nathomin chuckled and walked up behind the enchantress, snaked his hands around her and pulled her in close, kissing her neck tenderly. Malaehi turned her head and their gazes locked. For an eternal moment, ice met fire, love met hate, Koada’dal met Teir’dal... Malaehi knew at that moment, that she must decide.<br>
<br>
“I love you, Nathomin.” <br>
<br>
The rogue looked as if he‘d been struck, Malaehi had said it at last. He turned her completely around to face him, took her face gently into his hands, and kissed her slowly still staring into her eyes. But, something was wrong...<br>
<br>
Malaehi’s expression went cold, emotionless, even her voice ... it was like that of the undead. With a sense of foreboding, Nathomin continued his kiss, determined not to ruin this most precious time. Malaehi stood there is if she were the guardian statue. He pulled back in frustration, looking bewildered.<br>
<br>
“Nathomin... But, our love is not meant to be... and I cannot live in this torment anymore. The Ancients ... they will punish me for breaking my vow of chastity and taking a lover.” <br>
<br>
“I will end the life of anyone harming you, SsusZ’har” Nathomin said without blinking. He sighed and reached forward, but Malaehi stepped further, inches from the edge. The sound of pebbles dropping over the edge over the edge rang like sweet music in her elven ears as a feeling of euphoria entered Malaehi’s mind. She closed he eyes and swayed in the breeze.<br>
<br>
Nathomin’s eyes narrowed tightly, voice dropping to a cold whisper “What are you doing Malaehi d’Aeliu? Come here now,” pointing to his side.<br>
<br>
She could not hear him at all. All she could here was the soft sound of her Mother’s voice, singing a lullaby in the tongue of the Ancients. That was the most peaceful moment she had ever known, and all she wanted was that feeling again. Looking off Nathomin‘s shoulder, Malaehi‘s eyes glazed over with sheer madness. She envisioned her mother, standing off into the distance, opening her arms, beckoning her to come. <br>
<br>
“Ilhar Malaeliu...I’ve missed you so. Please.... I can’t take this anymore. I cannot live like this. The Ancients ... will see me bleed for my crimes ... I feel as if I am dead, Ilhar, please make it stop?” Tears poured down her face as the vision of her mother, turned her back and walked away. “Noooo, don’t leave me!!” The bitter laughed echoed in Malaehi’s mind, drowning out the sound of the approaching Giant.<br>
<br>
“Where is your Mother, lover? What is going on?!” Nathomin turned and faced the startled Giant, quickly grabbed his blades and set to work to destroy the intruder. Fear crept up the back of Nathomin’s spine. He quickly glanced over to his lover to see why she was not casting. That glance sent Nathomin reeling back as the Giant landed a crushing blow to his shoulder, rendering his left arm paralyzed and knocking him back several feet, away from Malaehi. He snarled, seeing the Giant turn his attention to his lover, then swiftly sliced his blade across the back of the Giant’s knees, through skin and tendons, crippling the roaring monster and sending it into a raging fury. Once on it had fallen half way, the rogue drove his blade into it’s back again and again, finally twisting his wrist up, puncturing a lung. The mountains echoed with the dying gasp of the felled Giant as Nathomin struggled to free his blade where it was deeply embedded.<br>
<br>
The air went completely still as Malaehi turned to face the setting sun. Nathomin left his buried blade, stood up on the Giant’s back, and immediately ran towards his lover. But, he reached her a moment too late, grabbing the sleeve of her pure, white robe which gave way freely as she stepped off the edge into oblivion, ending her life.<br>
<br>
&quot;Omnia vincit amor&quot; ~~ &quot;Love conquers all&quot; ~ Erollisi Marr, Goddess of Love<br>
